ol on ```https://google.com``` doesn't qualify those same permissions for ```http://malicious.com```. In the video that's attached labeled ```W7_Wildcard_Permissions.mp4```, you can see permissions are accepted on ```jsfiddle.net```, but are executed on ```exploit.html```.\n\nIn relation to the ```Crashing the Brave Browser \u0026 OS```, I've included a video titled ```W7_Chaos.mp4``` showing the script being able to launch a multitude of applications without limit. I cut the video short - as I'm sure it works well enough as PoC.\n\nThere is a file named ```exploit.html``` included. It has been edited to open three protocols, of which you can add more if you'd like. For example, change the code on line 30 ```var protocols = ['search:', 'telnet://towel.blinkenlights.nl', 'https://brave.com'];``` to ```var protocols = ['search:', 'telnet://towel.blinkenlights.nl', 'https://brave.com', 'ftp://']``` and that will launch FTP as well. If you'd like to enable ```chaos``` mode, which will open all the protocols on line 30 at once repetitively, change ```var chaos = false;``` to ```var chaos = true;```.\n\nThank you for your time!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-10-02T14:36:00.448Z","updated_at":"2018-10-02T14:36:00.448Z","actor":{"username":"mushicious","cleared":false,"url":"/mushicious","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/204/176/15c4dcfa63c1207c8af7901542f4b1d911d44f43_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":null},"attachments":[{"id":354315,"filename":"W7_Chaos.mp4","type":"video/mp4","url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/000/354/315/937172a6a5e4206876a911c27465e0c568706f4a/W7_Chaos.mp4?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22W7_Chaos.mp4%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27W7_Chaos.mp4\u0026response-content-type=video%2Fmp4\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AW